<%# ───────────────────────────── DATA FLOW DIAGRAMS ───────────────────────────── %>

<h2>Error Data Flow</h2>

<h3>Non-streaming (<code>react_component</code>)</h3>
<pre>
Component throws during renderToString (serverRenderReactComponent.ts)
         |
         +--- throwJsErrors == true? (currently: <%= throw_js_errors %>)
         |     YES: throw e → Node renderer returns error HTTP response
         |          → Ruby ALWAYS wraps as PrerenderError (rescue block, line 647)
         |          → errorReporter sees the error
         |     NO:  catch → return { hasErrors: true, html: errorHtml }
         |          → errorReporter does NOT see the error
         |
         v (if throwJsErrors was false)
Ruby helper.rb (non-streaming path, line 673):
  result["hasErrors"] && raise_on_prerender_error? (currently: <%= raise_on_prerender_error %>)
         |
         YES → raise PrerenderError → rescue_from handler
         NO  → render error HTML inline in page
</pre>

<h3>Streaming (<code>stream_react_component</code>)</h3>
<pre>
Component throws during renderToPipeableStream
         |
         v
onError / onShellError callback
         |
         v
reportError(error) → renderState.hasErrors = true
         |
         +--- throwJsErrors == true? (currently: <%= throw_js_errors %>)
         |     YES: emitError(error) → stream 'error' event
         |          → vm.ts handleStreamError → errorReporter.message()
         |     NO:  (no error event, errorReporter never sees it)
         |
         v
JSON chunk: { hasErrors: true, isShellReady: true|false }
         |  (renderState reset for next chunk)
         |
         v
Ruby helper.rb: should_raise_streaming_prerender_error?
         |
         +--- isShellReady == false? (shell error)
         |     Check: raise_on_prerender_error (currently: <%= raise_on_prerender_error %>)
         |
         +--- isShellReady == true? (post-shell / RSC error)
         |     Check: raise_non_shell_server_rendering_errors (currently: <%= raise_non_shell %>)
         |
         +--- Raise PrerenderError  OR  continue streaming
</pre>
